<HEADLINE>
BUDROYALE GETS LOW TOP WEIGHT FOR BIG 'CAP
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By KEVIN MODESTI  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   ARCADIA - Little separates Budroyale from General Challenge and
Cat Thief in the weight assignments announced Sunday for Saturday's
Santa Anita Handicap.
</P>
<P>
   As a result, nobody should have much complaint about rookie
racing secretary Michael Harlow's first Big 'Cap assignments, with
the possible exception of fans who like to see top horses tested by
heavy burdens.
</P>
<P>
   Budroyale will carry 122 pounds, General Challenge 121 and Cat
Thief 120. Malek, the 1998 Big 'Cap winner, and Puerto Madero are
next among likely starters at 118. Others: Dixie Dot Com, 117, and
Bagshot, 113.
</P>
<P>
   Budroyale's assignment is the lightest for a Big 'Cap highweight
since Helmsman (121) finished fourth behind Mr Purple (116) in
1996. The four-pound spread among the top five horses is the
tightest since 1994.
</P>
<P>
   ``Weight's never a concern (for the Budroyale camp),'' said
trainer Ted H. West, whose 7-year-old carried 121 to victory in the
San Antonio Handicap last time out.
</P>
<P>
   Tim Yakteen, assistant trainer of General Challenge, would have
liked to see his colt assigned the same weight as Breeders' Cup
Classic winner Cat Thief.
</P>
<P>
   ``But you're talking about a pound or two,'' Yakteen said.
</P>
<P>
   Entries for the $1 million, 1-mile race will be finalized
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   Antley's back (way back): Chris Antley, the 1999 Triple Crown
hero who hadn't ridden since the Nov. 6 Breeders' Cup because of
weight and knee trouble, returned to the races with a last-place
finish aboard Dance Master in Sunday's Baldwin Stakes at Santa
Anita.
</P>
<P>
   ``It felt great,'' Antley said despite finishing 15 lengths
behind winner Fortifier ($15.80) and jockey Brice Blanc in the
6-furlong race moved from the soggy turf to the sloppy main track.
</P>
<P>
   Antley said his weight is down to 119 pounds and he hopes to get
to 117 during the Santa Anita meet. He said it has been easier to
get back in shape than it was a year ago when he came back and rode
Charismatic to victories in the Kentucky Derby and Preakness.
</P>
<P>
   Notes: Two-year-old champion Anees covered 6 furlongs in 1:12 on
a ``good'' track, the fourth fastest of 22 workouts at the distance
Saturday, and is aiming to make the March 19 San Felipe his first
start since winning the Breeders' Cup Juvenile in November. ``This
horse is a lot fitter than people think,'' said Richard Mulhall,
racing manager for The Thoroughbred Corp. Anees would use the April
8 Santa Anita Derby as a prep for the May 6 Kentucky Derby....
Leading rider Corey Nakatani skipped his last two scheduled mounts
Sunday after telling the stewards he banged his left foot while
finishing last aboard Sparquita in the first race.... Equine nose
strips will become legal at California tracks Wednesday. Only five
of the 70 horses entered for that day's card at Santa Anita are
scheduled to wear the breathing aids.... Bella Chiarra, who used to
be trained by the late Charlie Whittingham in California, won the
Rampart Handicap at Gulfstream Park in Florida for Pat Byrne. Jack
Mandato owns the 5-year-old mare.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-02-28-00 0037EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
