<HEADLINE>
GO UNDERGROUND BUT STAY ON THE RUN
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By TOM HOFFARTH  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Sorry, but online registration for the City of Los
Angeles Marathon, the L.A. Bike Tour and the 5K run is closed. But
the official race Web site has a link to info available about
something new they call ``Metro Marathon'' - a way to be there in
person for the beginning, middle and end of the race by riding the
new connections of the Metro Red Line (www.mta.net).
</P>
<P>
   Other important notes about street closures, drink stations,
medical support and the all-you-can-eat, carbo-load dinner downtown
on Saturday are on the official site (www.lamarathon.com). Results
from the 1999 race are also there.
</P>
<P>
   _ Tiger Woods holds a one-hour golf exhibition that'll be
Webcast today at 10 a.m. from the driving range at La Costa, where
he finished the Andersen Consulting Match Play Championship final
Sunday. Find the event at the World Golf Championships site
(www.worldgolfchampionships.com/tigerexhibition).
</P>
<P>
   Meanwhile, a video game for PCs released recently by EA Sports
called Tiger Woods PGA Tour Collection allows gamers to go online
during PGA Tour events and compare their shots to Woods and others
in almost real-time. The site (www.playagainstthepros.com) has been
up since the Feb. 3 stop at Pebble Beach.
</P>
<P>
   _ Anthony Mason, the Charlotte Hornets forward apprehended by
authorities last weekend after a bar brawl, paid off at 8-1 odds on
one of the off-shore sportsbook sites (www.sportsbook.com) for the
prop bet of which NBA player would be the first to be arrested this
season. Mason was one of 17 players given odds.
</P>
<P>
   The site also lists a guilty verdict in a Ray Lewis murder trial
as a 3-5 wager.
</P>
<P>
   _ Don't have an autographed picture of Newy Scruggs hanging in
the rec room next to the dogs-playing-poker painting yet? Get one,
plus a free T-shirt, when you cough up $18 to join the official fan
club for the AM-1150 sports-talk host on his new multifaceted site
(www.newdawg.com).
</P>
<P>
   _ One-on-One Sports radio network, whose L.A. affiliate camps
out at KCTD-AM (1540), keeps an impressive vault of interviews that
its hosts have done over the last two weeks on its Web site
(www.1on1sports.com/audiovault.cfm).
</P>
</TEXT>
