<SLUG> BC-GADGETS-COLUMN0229-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    DVD changer offers Internet link
 &HT;    By James Cummings
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   DAYTON, Ohio _ First the problem was finding a way to store a
complete collection of phonograph records in a way that kept them
protected and made them easily accessible.
</P>
<P>
   Later the problem was eight-track tapes or cassette tapes or
videotapes, and now it's DVDs and CDs.
</P>
<P>
   But if your DVD and CD collection is getting out of hand and you
have about $5,000 to spend, Escient Inc. of Carmel, Ind., may have
a solution. The company's PowerPlay device can store up to 200
discs, and users can find and play any selection with the help of a
simple remote control.
</P>
<P>
   And if your collection grows beyond 200 discs, the PowerPlay
system can handle it. Additional changers to hold 200 discs each
are available for about $1,500 each. Up to 15 changers can be
linked to provide a system with 3,000 discs at once.
</P>
<P>
   But the PowerPlay does more than just store and play DVD and CD
discs; it also offers an Internet link that provides instant
information on all the discs in the collection.
</P>
<P>
   Escient maintains databases of 500,000 CDs and 3,000 DVD titles.
By linking to the site, users can click the remote control to
select a particular CD, and the system lists all the songs on the
CD as well as reviews and ratings. The DVD listings include
``chapters'' that mark scenes within movies plus movie reviews and
synopses.
</P>
<P>
   The Escient database divides movies and CDs into categories, so
users can browse only adventure movies or easy listening CDs, for
example. Users can also assign particular discs to custom
categories they design.
</P>
<P>
   The PowerPlay has all the normal connections found in high-end
DVD players, including VGA outputs for video and digital outputs
for audio.
</P>
<P>
   Plus it offers IEEE-1394 FireWire connections. FireWire is an
emerging technology that backers promise will simplify connections
between home theater components, computers and other home
electronic devices.
</P>
<P>
   PowerPlay is available through about 560 dealers nationally
including Audio Etc. in Beavercreek. The device last year won the
Electronic Lifestyles Manufacturer's Excellence Award for Best
Video Product for the Custom Electronic Design and Installation
Association, a trade group.
</P>
<P>
   Additional information on the company is available at
www.escient.com or by calling (800) 372-4368.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
