<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   NY-SHARPTON (New York) _ The up and down career of Al Sharpton
is clearly on the upswing after his peformance in the Diallo trial.
By Fred Kaplan. 995 words.
</P>
<P>
   BIGDIG-PROJECTS (Boston) _ Boston's ``Big Dig'' highway
rebuilding project, now running billions over budget, is just one
of many huge public works projects undertaken in recent years. By
Tina Cassidy. 960 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   MA-WORKERS (Boston) _ Massachusetts is renowned for universities
that educate the best and brightest in business. But neither the
state nor private companies are doing enough to help lower-skilled
workers get higher-level jobs. By Kimberly Blatnon. 1060 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; COMMENTARY (k) &LR;
</P>
