<HEADLINE>
AN INNOCENT MAN SLAIN BY POLICE IS REMEMBERED IN SONG 
</HEADLINE>
   (The Week in Review)  
 (NOTE TO INTERNATIONAL CLIENTS: For international clients' use by
special arrangement only. Asian and European points: contact Karl
Horwitz in Paris for details and prices (Phone: 47 42 17 11; FAX:
47-42-80-44). Latin American points: contact the Los Angeles office
(Phone: 310-996-0075; FAX: 310-996-0089)  
(bl) 
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   Within hours of the shooting of the 22-year-old Guinean
immigrant Amadou Diallo by four New York City police officers,
protests appeared in song. So far, black singers and rappers, white
folk singers and calypso artists have recorded music. Excerpted
lyrics follow.
</P>
<P>
   41 SHOTS
</P>
<P>
   By George Stass
</P>
<P>
   41 shots I can't understand.
</P>
<P>
   41 shots killed an innocent man.
</P>
<P>
   Outrage and disbelief throughout the land.
</P>
<P>
   41 shots explain if you can.
</P>
<P>
   48 hours to contemplate.
</P>
<P>
   48 to get their story straight.
</P>
<P>
   48 hours well isn't it great?
</P>
<P>
   If you are the law you get 48.
</P>
<P>
   AMADOU! (LOOK WHAT THEY'VE DONE TO YOU . . .)
</P>
<P>
   By Courtney
</P>
<P>
   John Wayne shooters rockin' hard dressed in blue
</P>
<P>
   ``Protect &AMP; Serve''
</P>
<P>
   But are they serving you?
</P>
<P>
   Abner Louima and now Amadou
</P>
<P>
   Countless others paid the price for you
</P>
<P>
   22/41 (AMADOU DIALLO'S SONG)
</P>
<P>
   By Stephen Smith
</P>
<P>
   Now 41 bullets ring out in a silence
</P>
<P>
   And forty one bullets have brought a man down
</P>
<P>
   And forty one bullets of longing exploded
</P>
<P>
   To leave four policemen regretting away . . .
</P>
<P>
   TEARS OF BLOOD
</P>
<P>
   By (Singing) Francine Edwards
</P>
<P>
   This should never happen again
</P>
<P>
   The price people have to pay
</P>
<P>
   I question the fact
</P>
<P>
   Is it because we black?
</P>
<P>
   . . . Take heed, hear my call, break down that blue wall and
give justice to one and all
</P>
<P>
   Forget black, white or brown and answer this question
</P>
<P>
   What would you have done if it was your son who never had a gun
or didn't have chance to run and four black police shoot him down
</P>
<P>
   Would they be arrested, would they be castrated or be praised
for a job well done?
</P>
<P>
   You'd be crying
</P>
<P>
   Tears, tears, crying tears of blood
</P>
</TEXT>
