   CHAIRMAKING-LIFEBEAT _ Perhaps it has something to do with our
goal-oriented American lifestyle, but many of today's travelers are
going on vacation not to relax and ``do nothing,'' but rather to
attempt an activity they've never tried before, learning new skills
along the way. A case in point: the 15 men, who traveled to Mike
Dunbar's Windsor institute, in Hampton, N.H., to learn how to make
sack-back Windsor chairs. By Matthew Holm. (1,100 words)
