</P>
<P>
   ANTIQUE-DARNERS-LIFEBEAT _ There was a time when no proper
household would be without at least one. As common as sadirons and
buttonhooks, they were regularly used by women, often by children,
occasionally by men. And, although they came in a seemingly
infinite number of shapes, sizes and materials, every one had the
same function _ to hold fabric taut while being darned. They are
stocking darners. By Wayne Muller. (1,000 words)
