<SLUG> BC-BODYSHAPER-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
IS POPULAR DIET POWDER WORTH ITS WEIGHT IN CLAIMS?
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By CAROLYN POIROT 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   FORT WORTH, Texas _ Just a tablespoon a day melts the fat away,
claim radio personalities offering testimonials for BodyShaper, the
weight-loss supplement currently taking the country by storm.
</P>
<P>
   On-air testimonials by radio personalities like KRLD/1080 AM's
Kate Delaney, ``the Sports Princess,'' and WBAP/820 AM's Hal Jay
are firing the sales of ``BodyShaper,'' a nutritional weight-loss
product distributed by Mark Nutritionals out of San Antonio.
BodyShaper helps you lose weight while you sleep, without
exercising or dieting, say on-air personalities from at least five
area stations, who say they've been losing weight using the product
in recent months.
</P>
<P>
   But not everyone is convinced that BodyShaper is such a good
idea.
</P>
<P>
   It's ``just a ridiculous scam,'' says Dr. Tim Gorski, an
Arlington obstetrician/gynecologist who serves as chairman of the
Dallas-Fort Worth Council Against Health Fraud and writes a monthly
column on medical misconceptions and deceptions for Tarrant County
Physician, official journal of the Tarrant County Medical Society.
</P>
<P>
   BodyShaper contains collagen, aloe vera and conjugated linoleic
acid (CLA, a mixture of polyunsaturated fats, also known as
``essential fatty acids''), according to Mark Nutritionals. It is
not a laxative, not a diuretic, and does not contain any form of
ephedrin to speed up metabolism, the company says.
</P>
<P>
   It contains nothing that can actually contribute to weight loss,
Gorski counters.
</P>
<P>
   ``It probably does `work,' but only because of the very specific
instructions that it is to be taken on an empty stomach, at
bedtime, no less than three hours after eating,'' Gorski says.
</P>
<P>
   The BodyShaper ``system'' requires that you take one tablespoon
of the pleasant-tasting, fruit-flavored supplement on an empty
stomach, at least three hours after eating, right before going to
bed. Nothing else except water is permitted during that time, and
additional water is recommended throughout the day.
</P>
<P>
   Gorski says he always tells patients trying to lose weight to
drink more water throughout the day and not to eat late at night,
but he doesn't charge them $48 a month for one tablespoon of
supplement per day.
</P>
<P>
   ``That's just outrageous. A glass of skim milk taken at bedtime
on an empty stomach would work as well and maybe even better than
BodyShaper,'' Gorski says.
</P>
<P>
   One month's supply (15 fluid ounces) costs $60, except for radio
listeners who are offered a $48 special.
</P>
<P>
   Mark Nutritionals also sells Atomic Energy, a stimulant to speed
up metabolism ($48 for a month's supply), Maximum Nutrition, a
combination of vitamins, minerals and nutritional herbs ($30), and
The Clicker activity counter to help people monitor how much
exercise they are getting throughout the day ($39.95 for one or $50
for two).
</P>
<P>
   Promoters say BodyShaper is ``a natural product that does not
stimulate, starve or trick the body into weight loss.'' They do not
deny the benefits of exercise, but they say the BodyShaper system
works even without it.
</P>
<P>
   Mark Nutritionals now has 60 full-time employees taking phone
orders, one of those employees said. She says she takes an average
of 300 calls a day.
</P>
<P>
   Telephone sales are fueled by radio ``testimonials,'' not
advertisements, she says.
</P>
<P>
   ``We recommend eating a healthy diet and getting exercise, but
if you can't exercise, it works anyway. I just got off the phone
with a woman from Fort Worth who has MS and can't exercise. We're
not telling people not to exercise. It's good if you can, but some
can't, and this works to help them lose weight anyway.''
</P>
<P>
   (Carolyn Poirot writes on health issues for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the
World Wide Web: www.star-telegram.com) nn
</P>
</TEXT>
