</P>
<P>
   COLLEGE
</P>
<P>
   BKC-AUBURN-PORTER _ Update on status of Auburn's Chris Porter.
(Barnhart, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   LEFTY-DRIESELL _ If Georgia State basketball coach Lefty
Driesell makes it to the NCAA Tournament this season, he would set
a record for longest time span between first and last tournament
appearances. It was 36 years ago that Driesell took Davidson to the
NCAAs. Now his Georgia State team can reach the tourney by winning
the TAAC tournament starting Wednesday. (Bradley, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   BOXING
</P>
<P>
   EVANDER _ Evander Holyfield says he spent a lot of time
pondering and studying boxing history before deciding that he will
indeed fight again, presumably in May vs. John Ruiz. (Bunn, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   OLYMPICS
</P>
<P>
   NATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   OLY-RECORDS _ ATLANTA _ The future of the Atlanta Olympic
records the newspapers and state attorney general fought so hard to
make public last year is in jeopardy. Atlanta Olympic officials
have dissolved their corporation and transferred ownership of
thousands of boxes of documents detailing the bid and organizing
committee operations to the Colorado Springs, Colo based USOC,
which will either transfer the records to Colorado or incinerate
them. Either option puts the vast majority of documented Olympic
history out of reach of the Atlanta public. (Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 18.
</P>
