</P>
<P>
   JACKSONVILLE, Texas _ All Maurice Miller, a Wal-Mart meat
cutter, wanted was a $2-an-hour raise. When he didn't get it, the
barrel-chested butcher took on the nation's biggest retailer _ and
won. In, of all places, anti-union East Texas, Miller, 45,
organized the country's first successful union vote in a Wal-Mart
store. By BARRY SHLACHTER. Story will move in ``a'' general news
