   ANCIENT CHINESE-AMERICAS &QL;
</P>
<P>
   FORT WORTH, Texas _ Mike Xu, who teaches Chinese Studies at
Texas Christian University, believes that writing samples of the
ancient Olmec people in southern Mexico show that Chinese from the
Shang Dynasty sailed to the Americas thousands of years ago and
influenced the Olmec. Xu is now reluctantly finding himself part of
an ongoing controversy over the evolution of culture in the
Americas. By PETE ALFANO. Story has moved in ``a'' general news
category. &QL; 
