   OSCAR-SUPPORTING ACTOR &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ No less an authority than gossip columnist Liz Smith
has chimed in on this year's Oscar race for Best Supporting Actor,
saying that 11-year-old Haley Joel Osment shouldn't be considered
because he hasn't toiled in the business for years like fellow
nominees Tom Cruise and Michael Caine. Last time anybody looked,
there was no minimum age for winning an Oscar, and Best Supporting
Actor was not a lifetime achievement award. By ROBERT PHILPOT.
Story will move in ``e'' entertainment category. &QL; 
