<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Bass to buy Bristol Hotels in deal worth $157 million
 &HT;    By Shelia M. Poole
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Bass PLC announced a deal Monday to buy Dallas-based
Bristol Hotels &AMP; Resorts Inc. for $9.50 a share, or $157 million.
</P>
<P>
   Bass already owns 9.9 percent of Bristol, which leases or
manages 112 hotels, most of them Holiday Inns. Bristol is also the
largest operator of Bass Hotels &AMP; Resorts properties in the world.
</P>
<P>
   The $9.50 a share Bass will pay for outstanding Bristol stock is
65 percent more than the company's closing price of $5.75 on
Friday.
</P>
<P>
   The deal has been approved by the Bristol board and is awaiting
shareholder approval. United/Harvey Holdings, which owns 39 percent
of Bristol's stock, has entered an agreement with Bass to accept
the offer. Bristol officials could not be reached for comment.
</P>
<P>
   Bass owns the Holiday Inn, Inter-Continental and Crowne Plaza
brands. The company's North American headquarters is in Atlanta.
</P>
<P>
   Thomas R. Oliver, chairman and chief executive of Bass Hotels &AMP;
Resorts, said the company sees ``significant growth prospects''
because of the marriage of strong brands and an expert management
system. ``Adding Bristol to our company effectively makes us one of
the leading hotel operators across all segments of the industry,''
he said.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
