celebrate his 14th birthday. OK, he was born 56 years ago. But
Tuesday is leap day, and he's sharing the occasion with scores of
other ``29ers'' in the self-styled Leap Year Capital of the World,
where a calendar's asterisk is accorded cult status. By MARTY
RACINE.
