<SLUG> BC-TEN-DAVIS-CUP-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
(DW)
</HEADLINE>
  
 McENROE GETS COMMITMENT FROM SAMPRAS FOR DAVIS CUP   By BRIAN FIDELMAN   
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   John McEnroe on Monday named his dream pairing, Pete Sampras and
Andre Agassi, to the Davis Cup team that will face the Czech
Republic in the quarterfinals in April.
</P>
<P>
   This is the lineup that the United States captain had planned
for the first-round match in Zimbabwe earlier this month. But
Sampras pulled out with a hip injury, and the United States barely
survived.
</P>
<P>
   McEnroe said he would name the team's other two players a few
weeks before the round, which will be played at the Great Western
Forum in Los Angeles from April 7-9. A favorite of McEnroe's is
Chris Woodruff, a 27-year-old Davis Cup rookie who was a
replacement in Zimbabwe. Woodruff lost his first singles match, but
withstood enormous pressure in the deciding match and saved
McEnroe's coaching debut with an emotional victory to give the
United States a 3-2 escape.
</P>
<P>
   ``I almost feel like it would be a shame if he wasn't on the
team,'' McEnroe said in a conference call. ``What he went out there
and accomplished is something I feel like was very special.''
</P>
<P>
   McEnroe has made no secret that he wants to see Sampras make a
greater commitment to Davis Cup.
</P>
<P>
   Asked whether there would be any lingering resentment among
other players toward Sampras that might affect team chemistry,
McEnroe said, ``I think that's my job in a sense, to try to build
team chemistry.''
</P>
<P>
   ``In general Pete has expressed mixed feelings himself, and the
people he's expressed it with in a lot of cases are the players
themselves,'' McEnroe said. ``The players are as aware or more
aware of his feelings than perhaps a lot of the people that follow
the Davis Cup or the officials around it.''
</P>
<P>
   Sampras will play in April (``Obviously a lot easier if you're
playing in Los Angeles to commit to that,'' McEnroe said), but a
victory over the Czech Republic would lead to a semifinal in Spain
or Russia. ``As far as I know, yes, he's absolutely committed to at
least the rest of this year and hopefully beyond that.''
</P>
<P>
   Sampras and Agassi have not played together in Davis Cup since
1995, the last time the United States won the cup.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
