<HEADLINE>
SHORT ITEMS ON TRAVEL DEALS  
 (FOR RELEASE SUNDAY, MARCH 5) 
</HEADLINE>
   (af)  
 By JANET PIORKO   
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   YELLOWSTONE IN SPRING
</P>
<P>
   Prices are discounted at Yellowstone National Park Lodges by as
much as 55 percent for various periods in spring. The discounts,
called Early Bird Specials, must be booked by April 1.
</P>
<P>
   The five lodges and their discounts are the Old Faithful Inn,
$89 to $99 for a premium room May 12 to 18; Mammoth Hot Springs
Hotel, $59 for a mid-range room May 5 to 18; Old Faithful Snow
Lodge, $99 for all rooms May 5 to 18; Grant Village, $69 for a
mid-range room May 26 to June 1, and the Lake Hotel, $99 for a
premium room May 19 to 25.
</P>
<P>
   Prices are good for one or two in a room. Other categories of
lodging are available at discounts in some cases. The properties
are operated by Amfac Parks and Resorts. Information and
reservations: (307) 344-7311 or on the Web,
www.travelyellowstone.com. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   CLIPPER SHIP DISCOUNTS
</P>
<P>
   Star Clippers has two-for-one savings for residents of the
Northeast and Florida on 12 selected voyages of its seven-night
spring and summer cruises from Barbados on the Star Clipper, a
360-foot four-masted sailing ship. On Aug. 6 and 20 and Sept. 3,
the least expensive inside cabin will be $1,654 for two people; on
nine other dates starting April 30, the inside cabin rate is $1,786
for two.
</P>
<P>
   The special rates are designed for those who are flying from New
York or Miami to Barbados. Air fare is additional. Built in 1992,
the ship can take 170 passengers; cabins are air-conditioned, and
there are two swimming pools. The cruise calls at Martinique, Iles
des Saintes, Antigua, St. Kitts, Dominica and St. Lucia.
Information: (800) 442-0551. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ASPEN IN APRIL
</P>
<P>
   April Spring Specials that include lodging and a six-day lift
ticket are available from April 7 to 23 from the Aspen Skiing Co.
and various Aspen-Snowmass properties; they must be purchased by
March 15. At the Aspen Mountain Lodge, a bed-and-breakfast on Main
Street, the price is $406 a person in double occupancy; at the
Hotel Jerome, also on Main Street, the price is $691.
</P>
<P>
   There are also discounts on lift tickets sold separately: for
example, during this period they are $75 for three days, $92 for
four days and $114 for six days. More information or reservations:
(888) 649-5982, or at www.skiaspen.com. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   WEEKEND AWAY
</P>
<P>
   Weekender rates offer discounts of up to 50 percent at more than
250 participating SRS-Worldhotels properties. Some hotels also
extend the rates to Thursday and Monday nights. The Harbour Plaza
Hotel in Hong Kong charges about $145 for a double room, the Pan
Pacific in Bangkok $125. The Savoy Hotel in Berlin charges $145 for
a double, the Plaza in Copenhagen $161 (prices may vary, depending
on exchange rates). A full list can be seen at
www.srs-worldhotels.com. Reservations and information: (800)
223-5652.
</P>
