<P>
   (NYT29) BOMBAY, India -- Feb. 28, 2000 -- INDIA-TECH-WORKERS --
Students having coffee at an Indian Institute of Technology campus
in Bombay. The schools, elite public universities here known as
IITs, produced the thousands of graduates who left for the United
States in the past. Today, having succeeded, many are returning as
entrepreneurs with money to spare, because there are economic
opportunities in the increasingly open Indian economy and because
the Hindu nationalist-led government that has been in power since
1998 is more open to their participation in the country's affairs.
(Celia Dugger/The New York Times)
</P>
