President Al Gore, visiting Pueblo, Colo., on Monday has a plan for
education that rules out vouchers. Underlying the platforms of all
four candidates is a central frustration: with the federal
government responsible for contributing only 7 cents of every
dollar spent in public schools, each candidate is struggling to
demonstrate how he would improve performance from a perch so
removed from the classroom. Paul Hosefros/The New York Times)
