   (NYT26) NEW YORK -- Feb. 28, 2000 -- SHOSTAKOVICH-THEATER-2 --
Simon McBurney, center, the aritistic director of the Theatre de
Complicite, working with the Emerson String Quartet at a rehearsal
of ``The Noise of Time'' at John Jay College Theater. The first
half of the production, kept more mysterious, uses four actors and
draws on documentary and archival material in a multimedia
presentation. ``It is not a reading, not a play,'' McBurney said.
``No one is pretending to be Shostakovich. Instead, we are
attempting to meditate on him, understanding that the 'him' will be
present in the 15th quartet.''(Ruby Washington/The New York Times)
