<P>
   (NYT25) NEW YORK -- Feb. 28, 2000 -- SHOSTAKOVICH-THEATER-1 --
Simon McBurney, in shirt-sleeves, directs ``The Noise of Time,'' at
John Jay College Theater, in which the Emerson String Quartet, turn
Shostakovich's 15th String Quartet into a spectacle. ``Acting at
its best is a musical profession,'' McBurney said recently. ``When
you act onstage, the musical function is almost more dominant than
the emotional one.'' Six performances are to be presented through
Sunday at the John Jay College Theater near Lincoln Center. (Ruby
Washington/The New York Times)
