<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-CORRECTIONS-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR TUESDAY, FEB. 29
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Tuesday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-TRADE-LABOR-NYT (moved on Thursday, Feb. 24)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Thursday, Feb. 24,
about the resignation of three labor leaders from a presidential
advisory panel on global trade misstated the title of one, Lenore
Miller. She is president emeritus of the Retail, Wholesale and
Department Store Union, not its current head.
</P>
<P>
   The article also misstated the acronym for the union led by Jay
Mazur, who also left the panel. It is Unite _ for Union of
Needletrades, Industrial and Textile Employees _ not United.
</P>
<P>
   BC-MCCAIN-PEROT-NYT (moved on Friday, Feb. 25)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Friday, Feb. 25,
about support for John McCain by Reform Party members misstated the
number of candidates seeking the Reform nomination for president.
Patrick J. Buchanan is among 12 who have notified the party that
they intend to pursue the nomination; he is not the only one.
</P>
<P>
   BC-NJ-SENATE-DEMS-NYT (moved on Sunday, Feb. 27)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Sunday, Feb. 27,
about the Democratic contest for United States Senate from New
Jersey misstated former Gov. Jim Florio's approval rating in a
survey released last week. The 39 percent figure was his favorable
rating among registered Democrats, according to the Quinnipiac
College Poll _ not his unfavorable one, which was 17 percent.
</P>
<P>
   BC-OBIT-TOBLER-NYT (moved on Sunday, Feb. 27)
</P>
<P>
   The obituary of Henry Jernigan Tobler, sent by the New York
Times News Service on Sunday, Feb. 27, misstated his age and the
year his leukemia was diagnosed. He was 33, not 34; he became ill
in 1994, not 1993.
</P>
<P>
   The obituary also misspelled the given name of his surviving
grandmother. She is Helene Tobler, not Helen.
</P>
<P>
   BC-IRWIN-DANCE-REVIEW-NYT (moved on Sunday, Feb. 27)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Sunday, Feb. 27,
about ``The Elegance of Tap and the Comedy of Tap,'' a performance
at Town Hall on Friday, misspelled the given name of a dancer who
made an unscheduled appearance. He is Baakari Wilder, not Baraki.
</P>
<P>
   BC-CIR-FREE-ISP-NYT (moved on Wednesday, Feb. 24)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Wednesday, Feb.
24, about free Internet service omitted an operating system that is
compatible with the Freewwweb service. The service works with
Macintosh as well as Windows computers.
</P>
</TEXT>
